Frontend developer, Engineer in automotive mechanics and graduated from INACAP as a programmer analyst. Trained to work as a web developer, with aspirations to improve knowledge mainly in the frontend area. Passionate about programming and currently looking for opportunities to continue growing in the area. I love Javascript ♡.
Centro de formación técnica INACAP - Programmer Analyst.
Instituto profesional DUOC UC - Engineer in automotive mechanics and autotronics.

Among my duties is to develop together with a team, a web application for a customer, using React.js, Typescript y Redux toolkit. For this purpose, each of the new features is created with their respective tests using Jest.js.

Among my duties were: Working on two different projects, in the first one I worked with React.js, with Apollo and material-ui, where my tasks are mainly in modifying existing features and fixing bugs in the web application. In the second project, I did it from scratch with Next.js technology, I was in charge of it, which meant working on it from scratch, building new features as required and managing and controlling bugs in the application.

Among my functions were: Developing new products with Vue.js, solving different features with Java or React Native, I also worked with PostgreSQL databases, as well as using AWS for the cloud service.
The job consisted of developing a website with React.js for the company together with a team of people.
